   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_01_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <salute>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DarnX1">
			  my dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DarnE1">Lady Darnley</persName>
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
            that I have given you<lb/>
            trouble by enclosing<lb/>
            the worthless heath in<lb/>
            the same box with the<lb/>
            Botany-bay-palm - But<lb/>
            may I beg the favor of<lb/>
            you to order your<lb/>
            gardener to have it<lb/>
            sent to Town to<lb/>
            N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. 51. Manchester S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.<lb/>
            for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Capt<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>. Beaufort</persName>,<lb/>
            and if your <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DarnE1">Ladyship</persName>
               <lb/>
            will have the goodness<lb/>
            to ask <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ClifX1">Lord Clifton</persName> to<lb/>
            frank &amp; forward the<lb/>
            enclosed note it will<lb/>
            inform him of the cause<lb/>
            of the delay -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>It will give me pleasure<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_01_page02.jpg"/>
               <del/> I am now at<lb/>
               <placeName ref="/.Placeography.xml#Black-Castle_IE">Black Castle</placeName> with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BuxtX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                  <lb/>
            Buxton</persName> who desires<lb/>
            to be kindly remembered<lb/>
            to your Ladyship<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
            With best Compliments<lb/>
            to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DarnJ1">Lord Darnley</persName> and<lb/>
            to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BligX1">Lady E Bligh</persName>
               <lb/>
            I am<lb/>
            My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DarnE1">Lady Darnley</persName>
               <lb/>
            your Ladyships<lb/>
            Affec<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Servant<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
